      <section eId="sec_1914">
        <num>1914</num>
        <heading>Reporting</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the number and identity of communities and local governments\nreached through the comprehensive education, engagement and outreach\neffort;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the number of regional discussion forums held for communities and\ndevelopers, and identification of attendees and description of outcomes;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the number, description and status of renewable energy planning\ntools and resources developed, including the clean energy development\nmapping tool;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the number and identity of local governments receiving technical\nassistance and training on the clean energy mapping tool and other\nresources;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_e">
          <num>(e)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the number of service providers and contracts awarded;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_f">
          <num>(f)</num>
          <content>
            <p>the amount of funds invested in the clean energy outreach and\ncommunity planning program; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1914__subsec_g">
          <num>(g)</num>
          <content>
            <p>any additional information relevant to assessing program\neffectiveness.\n  2. The authority shall submit such report to the governor, the\ntemporary president of the senate, and the speaker of the assembly. A\ncopy of the report shall also be posted on the authority's website.\n  * NB Repealed December 31, 2031\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
